snippet.textDisplay:
I watched this on the After Party, I've watched it twice in theaters, and I'm watching it now-- This scene still cracks me up. I cried with laughter and had to cover my mouth whenever I first watched this in theatres. 😂 Joe is the treasure of the film.. which is probably how he got lost in the first place. "Goonies" inspired him to go search for some treasure, but when he addressed the boys about it, they said, "Joe, it's just a movie! There is no treasure!"
So, Joe, being Joe, went out and ventured out on his own to find this treasure, got lost.
As a result, "Damned" was created.
Somewhere along the way, they realized that friendship was the real treasure and Murr shouldn't make movies. 😜
